====================================================================
🏏 CRICKET FIELD WEBSITE PROJECT
====================================================================

📌 Project Objective:
---------------------
Build a responsive cricket-themed website using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The goal is to enhance frontend development skills including:
- HTML form creation
- CSS styling and responsive layouts using Flexbox and Grid
- JavaScript DOM manipulation and event handling

🎯 Key Features:
----------------
✅ Responsive webpage layout using Flexbox and CSS Grid  
✅ Cricket-themed content with live scores and news section  
✅ Contact form with client-side JavaScript validation  
✅ Dynamic image gallery where users can upload cricket images  
✅ Clean and modern UI with accessibility in mind  

📁 File Structure:
------------------
- index.html       → Main website file with content structure
- style.css        → CSS file for layout, design, and responsiveness
- script.js        → JavaScript for form validation and image upload logic
- README.txt       → Project overview and documentation

🧪 How to Run the Project:
---------------------------
1. Download or clone the repository:
   https://github.com/yourusername/cricket-field-website

2. Open the folder in a code editor (e.g., VS Code)

3. Open `index.html` in a browser:
   - You will see a welcome message and a cricket-themed layout
   - Scroll down to test the image gallery and contact form

4. Upload local cricket images using the "Add Image" button  
5. Submit the contact form with valid inputs to test validation

🧰 Technologies Used:
----------------------
- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox & Grid)
- JavaScript (ES6)
- FileReader API

📱 Responsive Design:
---------------------
- Works well on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices
- Navigation and layout adjust with screen size

🙌 Acknowledgements:
---------------------
This project was created to practice and demonstrate core web development skills.
Ideal for beginners learning DOM manipulation and responsive UI.

📬 Contact:
-----------
For suggestions or collaboration, reach out via the contact form on the site!

